      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:4:13:2",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) لَا تُفَتِّشِ النَّاسَ فَتَبْقَى بِلَا صَدِيقٍ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad Bin Isa, from Ali Bin Al Hakam and Muhammad Bin Sinan, from Ali Bin Abu Hamza, from Abu Baseer who said, ",
          "‘Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘Do not investigate the people, for you would remain without a friend’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad ibn ‘Isa from Ali ibn al-Hakam and Muhammad ibn Sinan from, Ali ibn abu Hamza from abu Basir who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) has said, ‘Do not be a spy against people; you will remain without friends.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
